        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "δὲ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but) The antithesis is between his intention of travelling to see them, and the doctrine itself. The external change of that intention for good reasons infers no inconsistency in the doctrine. In the mean time, Paul shows, that those who are light [fickle] in external matters are wont to be, and to appear to be, light also in things spiritual.—",
        "children": []
      },
