        "text": "one",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " thing which involved an indubitable \"yea,\" namely, my preaching to you. In that, at any rate, there was nothing capricious, nothing variable, nothing vacillating. St. Paul, in a manner characteristic to his moods of deepest emotion, \"goes off at a word.\" The Corinthians talked of his \"yea\" and \"nay\" as though one was little better than the other, and neither could be depended on; well, at any rate, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "one thing",
